What is the correct way to instantiate a class?
class Car {
    String model;
},Car c = new Car()

What is the output?
class Test {
    int x = 10;
}
Test t1 = new Test();
Test t2 = t1;
t2.x = 20;
System.out.println(t1.x);,20,10,Compilation error,NullPointerException

What happens with this code?
String s1 = "Hello";
String s2 = s1;
s1 = "World";
System.out.println(s2);,Hello,World,HelloWorld,Compilation error

What is the result?
class Outer {
    int x = 10;
    class Inner {
        void display() {
            System.out.println(x);
        }
    }
},10,Compilation error,0,NullPointerException

What happens with null reference?
String s = null;
System.out.println(s.length());,NullPointerException,Prints 0,Prints null,Compilation error

How do you instantiate an inner class?
class Outer {
    class Inner {}
},Outer.Inner in = new Outer().new Inner()

What is the output?
class Test {
    static int count = 0;
    Test() {
        count++;
    }
}
new Test();
new Test();
System.out.println(Test.count);,2,0,1,Compilation error

What is the result?
class Box {
    int size;
    Box(int s) { size = s; }
}
Box b;
System.out.println(b.size);,Compilation error (variable not initialized),0,NullPointerException,Prints null

What happens when reassigning object references?
Dog d1 = new Dog("Max");
Dog d2 = new Dog("Buddy");
d1 = d2;,Original Max object is eligible for GC,Both objects remain in memory,d2 becomes null,Compilation error

What is the output?
class Test {
    int x;
}
Test t = new Test();
System.out.println(t.x);,0,null,Compilation error,Undefined

What happens with this code?
class Outer {
    static class Nested {
        int x = 10;
    }
}
Outer.Nested n = new Outer.Nested();
System.out.println(n.x);,10,Compilation error,0,NullPointerException

What is the result?
StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder("Java");
StringBuilder sb2 = sb;
sb2.append(" 17");
System.out.println(sb);,Java 17,Java,Compilation error,17

What is the output?
class Test {
    Test() {
        System.out.println("Created");
    }
}
Test t = new Test();,Created,Nothing is printed,Compilation error,Test

What happens with method-local inner class?
class Outer {
    void method() {
        class Local {
            int x = 10;
        }
        Local l = new Local();
        System.out.println(l.x);
    }
},Prints 10,Compilation error,NullPointerException,0

What is the result?
Object obj = new Object();
obj = null;,obj is eligible for GC,obj still references the object,Compilation error,NullPointerException immediately

What is the output?
class A {
    int x = 5;
}
A a1 = new A();
A a2 = new A();
a1 = a2;
a2.x = 10;
System.out.println(a1.x);,10,5,15,Compilation error

What is the result?
class Outer {
    int x = 10;
    static class Nested {
        void display() {
            System.out.println(x);
        }
    }
},Compilation error (cannot access non-static from static),10,0,NullPointerException

What happens with this code?
String s = new String("Hello");
s = s.concat(" World");
System.out.println(s);,Hello World,Hello,World,Compilation error

What is the output?
class Test {
    int x = 10;
    void display() {
        int x = 20;
        System.out.println(x);
    }
}
new Test().display();,20,10,30,Compilation error

What is the result?
Integer i1 = new Integer(100);
Integer i2 = new Integer(100);
System.out.println(i1 == i2);,false,true,Compilation error,NullPointerException

What is the output?
class Outer {
    int x = 5;
    class Inner {
        int x = 10;
        void display() {
            System.out.println(Outer.this.x);
        }
    }
},5,10,15,Compilation error

What is the result?
class Test {
    int x;
    Test(int x) {
        this.x = x;
    }
}
Test t = new Test(5);
System.out.println(t.x);,5,0,Compilation error,NullPointerException

What happens with circular references?
class A { B b; }
class B { A a; }
A a = new A();
B b = new B();
a.b = b;
b.a = a;
a = null;
b = null;,Both objects eligible for GC,Neither object can be GC'd,Only A is eligible for GC,Only B is eligible for GC

What is the output?
class Test {
    static int x = 10;
}
Test t1 = new Test();
Test t2 = new Test();
t1.x = 20;
System.out.println(t2.x);,20,10,30,Compilation error

What is the result?
class Box {
    int size = 10;
}
Box b1 = new Box();
Box b2 = b1;
b1 = null;
System.out.println(b2.size);,10,NullPointerException,Compilation error,0

What is the output?
class Test {
    {
        System.out.println("Block");
    }
    Test() {
        System.out.println("Constructor");
    }
}
new Test();,Block Constructor,Constructor Block,Constructor,Block
